Many US companies check the credit ratings of potential employees; the
result is that anyone who becomes unemployed and falls behind on bills
does not get hired again.

http://www.miller-mccune.com/business-economics/credit-report-dogging-job-seekers-31834/

While this is a crowning unfairness, fixing this would at best mean
that some people rotate more often in and out of unemployment.  The US must
do more to help the long-term unemployed and underemployed.

-- 
