Tennessee has imposed stiff censorship on the Internet, by banning the
posting of images that are likely to "cause emotional distress" to
someone.

http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/news/2011/06/tenn-law-bans-posting-images-that-cause-emotional-distress.ars

Will antiabortionists be prosecuted for posting images of fetuses?
(They certainly should know that these images can cause emotional
distress.)  Probably not &mdash; because the ban will be selectively
enforced by right-wing Christians.

